  "adaptive.infoTitle": "Latency controls",
  "adaptive.infoBody": "This panel now mixes two kinds of controls.<br><br><strong>Global far actions</strong> apply whenever latency drift exceeds the <strong>Far Threshold</strong>, even if adaptive resampling is off.<br><strong>Far Threshold</strong>: error threshold, in milliseconds of buffer drift, where far-mode actions become eligible.<br><strong>Hard recover high in far mode</strong>: aggressively drops buffered audio to return toward the target faster when latency is too high.<br><strong>Hard recover low in far mode</strong>: temporarily mutes output and rebuilds buffer latency when it falls too low, then stabilizes before fade-in.<br><strong>Silence in Far Mode</strong>: mutes output while far-mode recovery is active.<br><strong>Fade-In on Near Return</strong>: fade applied when far-mode muting ends and playback becomes audible again.<br><br><strong>Local resampling controller</strong> only applies when <strong>Adaptive resampling</strong> is enabled.<br><strong>Update interval</strong>: how often the PI controller updates, in audio callbacks.<br><strong>Adaptive Max</strong>: maximum correction clamp applied to the local resampling ratio.<br><strong>Adaptive KP</strong>: proportional gain. Higher values react faster to instantaneous buffer error.<br><strong>Adaptive Ki</strong>: integral gain. It corrects long-term bias and clock mismatch.<br><strong>Integral discharge</strong>: fraction of stored integral retained when the error changes sign. Lower values dump old controller energy more aggressively.<br><br><strong>Pause</strong> freezes the resampling controller, and <strong>Reset ratio</strong> is available while paused to return the ratio to neutral.",
  "telemetry.infoButton": "Latency panel info",
  "telemetry.toggle": "Show latency controls",
  "telemetry.targetMarkerTitle": "Latency gauge target marker",
  "telemetry.thresholdMarkerTitle": "Latency gauge far threshold marker",
  "telemetry.resampleMarkerTitle": "Resample gauge near max marker",
  "telemetry.infoTitle": "Latency Gauges",
  "telemetry.infoBody": "<strong>raw</strong>: instantaneous measured latency. The min/max markers show the recent sliding window.<br><br><strong>ctrl</strong>: smoothed latency used internally by the adaptive controller.<br><br><strong>resample</strong>: current adaptive resampling correction around the neutral 1.0 ratio. Left means slower, right means faster.",
